00:56:55.320 --> 00:57:02.320
That is an agreement that I make with my partners at the beginning of the project.

00:57:02.320 --> 00:57:13.320
We come, we make, you know, just has to be a straightforward calculation. It has to be A times B times C or something like that.

00:57:14.320 --> 00:57:34.320
And then we can clearly measure the A and the B and the Cs, right? So for a given project, and if we are not able to get to that upfront, we are not able to agree on the A's and the B's and the C's and the D's, then I know there is a lesser chance of success.

00:57:35.320 --> 00:57:51.320
If my partner or the business team is clearly able to say, these are the A's that multiplied by the B's gives us the value. And the current value of A is X1. And if we increase that to X2, that can just get plugged back into the equation.

00:57:51.320 --> 00:57:58.320
